52.4	Anatole_France	Anatole France	Anatole France (16 April 1844 – 12 October 1924), born François-Anatole Thibault, , was a French poet, journalist, and novelist. He was born in Paris, and died in Saint-Cyr-sur-Loire. He was a successful novelist, with several best-sellers. Ironic and skeptical, he was considered in his day the ideal French man of letters. He was a member of the Académie française, and won the Nobel Prize for Literature in recognition of his literary achievements.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/1/13/Anatole_FranceA.jpg
